# Web (`apps/web`)

## Stack

Next.js 16 (Turbopack dev), React 19, Tailwind 4, Better Auth client, TanStack Query where used.

## App routes (`app/`)

- `/`, `/verify`, `/login`
- `/dashboard`, `/dashboard/keys`, `/dashboard/settings` (billing + account)
- `/bot/billing/success` — Paystack redirect; query: `via=telegram`, Paystack adds `reference` / `trxref`

## Env (detail in `apps/web/README.md`)

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` — browser + server API origin (no trailing slash).
- **`WEB_VERIFY_INTERNAL_SECRET`** — server-only; must match API; **never** `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.
- `WEB_APP_URL` — canonical site URL.
- Optional `API_BASE_URL` for server components/route handlers calling the API.

## UI patterns

- **`SiteNav`** on marketing-style pages.
- Design tokens: CSS variables + Tailwind e.g. `border-(--border)`, `text-(--text-2)`, `hover:bg-(--bg-subtle)`.
- Dashboard: `components/dashboard/*` — shell, API keys, settings/billing, Pro CTAs, docs snippets.

## Security

- **`POST /api/verify-lookup`** (or equivalent BFF): runs **only on server**; forwards to API with internal secret. Do not expose that secret to client bundles.

See **`9jacheckr-overview.mdc`** for full handbook.
